            <description><![CDATA[<p>Release date: 2026-06-26</p>
<p>This update makes Watch Folders more reliable after folder changes
and makes MLX and Keychain setup recovery clearer.</p>
<h2 id="new">New</h2>
<h2 id="improvements">Improvements</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Clearer MLX runtime setup.</strong> When a selected MLX
model is ready but the runtime still needs installation, Settings now
shows an inline setup prompt with an Install MLX runtime action.</li>
<li><strong>Clearer empty Watch Folder state.</strong> The sidebar now
says No folders when no watched folders are configured, and file
locations are easier for help and accessibility tools to identify.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="bug-fixes">Bug Fixes</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Fixed stale Watch Folder files appearing in All
Files.</strong> Removing, resetting, or repairing Watch Folders now
keeps the library, search index, and selection counts aligned so old
tracked items do not keep showing up.</li>
<li><strong>Fixed Watch Folder views falling back to the wrong
scope.</strong> Folder-based views now stay limited to the active
watched folders instead of accidentally showing the broader library
after stale selections.</li>
<li><strong>Fixed Keychain retry buttons for locked keychains.</strong>
Retry now opens the macOS unlock prompt instead of repeating a check
that could never unlock the keychain.</li>
</ul>
]]></description>
